	('e8bffc6d-36b4-438c-a6cd-a2f7d0723e54', 'Zoo Explorers 2026: What are Animals Eating', 'Buy Now! What are Animals Eating? Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!  Zoo Explorers Calling all little explorers – get ready for some big adventures with the Zoo!   Ever wonder where the Zoo animal food comes from? Curious about when our animals see the “doctor”? In this exciting drop off program for kids 4-6 years old, we’ll visit zoo animal areas, exhibits and more to explore something new about the Zoo each week!  Each Zoo Explorers program is 2 hours and will include zoo walks, hands on activities and guided experiences around the Zoo.  Prices Members: $45 Non-members: $50  Buy Now!         ZOO EXPLORERS 2026 SCHEDULE        Zoo Explorers 2026: Animal Training March 30, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo and learn how animal staff train our animals, then practice being a keeper and an animal!      Zoo Explorers 2026: What are Animals Eating? April 6, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!       @      Zoo Explorers 2026: Animal Training May 4, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!     Zoo Explorers 2026: What are Animals Eating May 11, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!    ', '2026-05-11 14:00:00+00', '2026-05-11 16:00:00+00', 'America/New_York', 'Zoo', NULL, '4f546c98-7985-4127-b472-c43254eb77c3', 38.2051766, -85.7053359, 4, 6, 45.00, false, 'https://louisvillezoo.org/event/zoo-explorers-2026-animal-training-may-11/', 'Louisville Zoo Events', 'f0386301-e604-479b-bf96-7d55cb4662d5', '["https://louisvillezoo.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/2026-Zoo-Explorers_What-are-Animal