	('4a533146-971e-4f7d-ab92-ad05f8df2a32', 'Single Day Camp - May 19, 2026 "Jaws and Claws" - SOLD OUT', 'Program designed for ages Kindergarten through 2nd Grade Dive into the world of powerful adaptations. Campers will examine how animals use their jaws and claws in sometimes unexpected ways, from tigers gently carrying cubs to armadillos digging with precision.  Prices Members: $70 Non-Members: $75  REGISTER ONLINE', '2026-05-19 12:30:00+00', '2026-05-19 21:00:00+00', 'America/New_York', 'Louisville Zoo, 1100 Trevilian Way, Louisville, KY, 40213, United States', 'Louisville Zoo, 1100 Trevilian Way, Louisville, KY, 40213, United States', '4f546c98-7985-4127-b472-c43254eb77c3', 38.2527000, -85.7585000, 5, 8, 70.00, false, 'https://louisvillezoo.org/event/single-day-camp-may-19-2026-jaws-and-claws/', 'Louisville Zoo Events', 'f0386301-e604-479b-bf96-7d55cb4662d5', '["https://louisvillezoo.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026-Single-Day-Camp-Header_Jaws-and-Claws.jpg"]', 'published', 0.650, NULL, false, 0, '''1100'':62,72 ''19'':5 ''2026'':6 ''2nd'':18 ''40213'':67,77 ''70'':53 ''75'':57 ''adapt'':26 ''age'':15 ''anim'':31 ''armadillo'':47 ''camp'':3 ''camper'':27 ''carri'':44 ''claw'':9,36 ''cub'':45 ''day'':2 ''design'':13 ''dig'':48 ''dive'':20 ''examin'':29 ''gentl'':43 ''grade'':19 ''jaw'':7,34 ''kindergarten'':16 ''ky'':66,76 ''louisvill'':60,65,70,75 ''may'':4 ''member'':52,56 ''non'':55 ''non-memb'':54 ''onlin'':59 ''power'':25 ''precis'':50 ''price'':51 ''program'':12 ''regist'':58 ''singl'':1 ''sold'':10 ''sometim'':38 ''state'':69,79 ''tiger'':42 ''trevilian'':63,73 ''unexpect'':39 ''unit'':68,78 ''use'':32 ''way'':40,64,74 ''world'':23 ''zoo'':61,71', '2026-05-10 16:01:11.923607+00', '2026-05-10 19:05:59.085041+00', 'openai', true),
	('a4653427-602d-4ea8-a538-3e2b716fc83a', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Animal Tales - Red Panda Exhibit', 'Animal Tales Join us at select animal exhibits to hear a story and test your animal imitation skills with a movement activity!  Guests can join us at selected animal exhibits for a story time throughout the spring. We’ll read 1 or 2 books and practice our animal imitation skills with a movement challenge related to the animal we’re featuring each week. See below for the dates, times, featured animals, and book selections.  HerpAquarium Books  All The Love in The World written by Rose Bunting and illustrated by Olivia Chin Mueller How This Book Got Red written by Margaret Chiu Greanias and illustrated by Melissa Iwai  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 2