	('44f13d11-c89a-44e6-b66f-c889dbd4e6c8', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Playtime in the Cub House', 'Playtime in the Cub House Stop in and enjoy some free play time in the Cub House presented by PNC. Meet other zoo friends and play in our space, the snow leopards might even peek in to play hide and seek with you through the exhibit glass. We will open the Cub House for unstructured play time select Saturday mornings. The space will open for up to 30 people at a time to play from 10:00 a.m. to 11:30 a.m.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '2026-05-23 14:00:00+00', '2026-05-23 15:30:00+00', 'America/New_York', 'Cub House at Louisville Zoo', NULL, '4f546c98-7985-4127-b472-c43254eb77c3', 38.2527000, -85.7585000, 0, 5,