	('1d4ca902-3d98-4420-a321-c9b49b9bf56e', 'ab7ebe6b-78de-4574-8909-6e292bac7425', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Celebrate Mother’s Day at the Louisville Zoo', 'Treat mom to a special day at the Zoo. In celebration of Mother’s Day, all mothers (and expecting mothers!) receive FREE Zoo admission on Sunday, May 10.  Spend the day exploring exhibits, watching animals enjoy the spring weather and making memories together as a family. From beloved animal moms to Zoo-wide experiences, there is something for everyone to enjoy.  How it works   Free admission is available to all mothers on Mother’s Day Tickets are available at the Zoo only Valid for standard daytime admission Zoo hours and regular parking fees apply.   Mother’s Day Specialty Drink  In honor of Mother’s Day Weekend, SSA will offer a special made‑to‑order Mother’s Day Mimosa, available for a limited time throughout the Zoo. This seasonal specialty is part of a new offering designed to give guests something a little different on select high‑traffic days. The Mother’s Day Mimosa will be available at multiple locations across the park for $10.99, while supplies last', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "All mothers receive FREE Zoo admission on Mother’s Day.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event takes place at the Zoo, which is an outdoor venue.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "holiday", "reason": "The event celebrates Mother’s Day.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is designed for families to spend time together.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The event is suitable for families with children of all ages.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "teen-friendly", "reason": "The event offers activities that can engage teenagers.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is classified as free due to complimentary admission for mothers, and it is family-oriented, taking place outdoors at the zoo to celebrate Mother''s Day.', NULL, 6413, '2026-05-10 16:00:12.134792+00'),
	('c8cac7fc-ec71-427b-a996-2aca892a3096', 'e8bffc6d-36b4-438c-a6cd-a2f7d0723e54', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Zoo Explorers 2026: What are Animals Eating', 'Buy Now! What are Animals Eating? Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!  Zoo Explorers Calling all little explorers – get ready for some big adventures with the Zoo!   Ever wonder where the Zoo animal food comes from? Curious about when our animals see the “doctor”? In this exciting drop off program for kids 4-6 years old, we’ll visit zoo animal areas, exhibits and more to explore something new about the Zoo each week!  Each Zoo Explorers program is 2 hours and will include zoo walks, hands on activities and guided experiences around the Zoo.  Prices Members: $45 Non-members: $50  Buy Now!         ZOO EXPLORERS 2026 SCHEDULE        Zoo Explorers 2026: Animal Training March 30, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo and learn how animal staff train our animals, then practice being a keeper and an animal!      Zoo Explorers 2026: What are Animals Eating? April 6, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!       @      Zoo Explorers 2026: Animal Training May 4, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!     Zoo Explorers 2026: What are Animals Eating May 11, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Explore the Zoo to see what the animals are munching on, if their breakfast is as tasty as ours, and where their leftovers go!    ', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The event is specifically designed for kids aged 4-6 years old.", "confidence": 0.95, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "The program includes hands-on activities and guided experiences to learn about animals.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The program focuses on animals and their natural behaviors.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event takes place at the zoo, which is an outdoor venue.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event encourages family participation and exploration.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "weekend", "reason": "The event is scheduled on weekends.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": 50, "age_max": 6, "age_min": 4, "is_free": false, "venue_name": "Zoo"}', 'The event is an educational program for young children at the zoo, focusing on animal diets and behaviors, with a price point indicating it is not free.', NULL, 8421, '2026-05-10 16:00:21.136313+00'),
	('be911967-f047-4a44-b3bc-24ffb8a7fad5', '696d8438-686d-42fc-99e8-3cb37e40d2f0', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Animal Tales - Tiger Taiga', 'Animal Tales Join us at select animal exhibits to hear a story and test your animal imitation skills with a movement activity!  Guests can join us at selected animal exhibits for a story time throughout the spring. We’ll read 1 or 2 books and practice our animal imitation skills with a movement challenge related to the animal we’re featuring each week. See below for the dates, times, featured animals, and book selections.  HerpAquarium Books  Tiger Tiger written and illustrated by Jonny Lambert Mr. Brown’s Bad Day written by Lou Peacock and illustrated by Alison Friend  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with Louisville Zoo membership or admission.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The event is designed for young learners and families.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "storytime", "reason": "The event includes story readings at animal exhibits.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "The program invites children to learn about animals through stories and activities.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is a family-oriented program at the zoo.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event takes place in a zoo setting, focusing on animals.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": 5, "age_min": 0, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is a free educational program for young children featuring storytime and animal activities at the Louisville Zoo, making it suitable for toddlers and families.', NULL, 5499, '2026-05-10 16:00:27.639698+00'),
	('b5e96630-bce1-4098-8252-7fc58cc81e27', '70047b7e-f06b-46ee-b632-2f25e3a2ea6e', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Litter Critters', 'Litter Critters Plastic is everywhere! Join us at our Litter Critter stations to learn how plastic waste effects animals and humans here in Kentucky and around the world. We’ll play games focused on recycling to earn a special sticker! These stations will be in the MetaZoo or the HerpAquarium on Wednesday afternoons in the spring.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with Louisville Zoo membership or admission.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The program is designed for young learners.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Participants will learn about plastic waste and its effects.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event invites families to play, observe, and learn together.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event focuses on environmental education regarding plastic waste.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "storytime", "reason": "Includes story readings as part of the activities.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": 5, "age_min": 0, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is a free educational program for young children at the Louisville Zoo, focusing on environmental awareness and includes various interactive activities.', NULL, 5794, '2026-05-10 16:00:33.721321+00'),
	('5813b222-4125-4ad2-925c-512052c35082', '501d921d-41e0-49bd-a96c-8c2d6e9976f5', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Wild Workout: Yoga (Flamingos) - SOLD OUT', 'BUY NOW! Gate opens at 6 p.m. |  Class begins at 6:30 p.m.  Join the flamboyance during this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout. Focus on controlled movements as flamingos showcase the art of poise and balance nearby.    Join us for yoga in the wild! We’re partnering with Flex Appeal to continue special Wild Workouts at your Zoo this year. We will be offering five unique outdoor yoga classes after the Zoo closes, so you can stretch in some of your favorite exhibit spaces.  For beginners and seasoned practitioners alike, these yoga classes are designed to help you increase flexibility, strengthen muscles, and improve overall health and recovery. Closed-toed shoes are strongly encouraged. Guests are also encouraged to bring a refillable water bottle that can be used at the bottle refill stations around the Zoo.  Classes are $25 each, plus a processing fee, and are available online only. All fitness levels and abilities are welcome. Tickets must be purchased online prior to the workout in order to attend.  The front gate opens at 6:00 p.m. Classes begin at 6:30 p.m.  Yoga classes on sale now! Pilates and Barre coming soon.  Prices $25 per person plus processing fee  Classes sold out in 2025 — Reserve your spot early!         FITNESS EVENTS        Throo the Zoo 5K Run/Walk 2026 May 9, 2026 @ 8:00 am  Race on over for the WILDEST 5K in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you on a safari directly “throo” the Zoo! Participants receive a t-shirt, finishers medal, post-race refreshments, PLUS a ticket to visit the Zoo at a much slower pace!       Wild Workout: Yoga (Flamingos) – SOLD OUT May 13, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Join the flamboyance during this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout. Focus on controlled movements as flamingos showcase the art of poise and balance nearby.     Wild Workout: Pilates (Red Panda) – SOLD OUT June 3, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Admire and imitate the graceful balance of our red pandas as you stretch and unwind in front of this forested exhibit space.     Wild Workout: Yoga (Glacier Run) June 22, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Join us in the arctic-inspired town of Glacier Run where you may see a grizzly or polar bear wandering about. It doesn’t matter if you can BEARly touch your toes, this workout is perfect for all fitness levels.      Wild Workout: Pilates (Giraffe) July 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on.     Wild Workout: Yoga (Butterfly) July 22, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Stretch your wings alongside our butterflies during this peaceful yoga session. Flitter inside our butterfly habitat post-workout to enjoy your animal inspiration up-close.      Wild Workout: Yoga (Colobus) August 1, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Swing by and enjoy this one-of-a-kind workout after the Zoo closes. Increase your flexibility as you enjoy the sights and sounds of our colobus monkey family peering at you from their lush habitat.      Wild Workout: Pilates (Little Penguin) August 19, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Enjoy a low-impact, muscle strengthening workout as our playful little penguins look on.      Wild Workout: Yoga (Giraffe) September 1, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on. These gentle giants will soothe your mind and help you find inner peace after a long day     Wild Workout: Pilates (Pinniped) September 9, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find your flow at this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout as you watch our playful pinnipeds (seals and sea lions).     Throo the Boo 2026 November 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Dash over and join us for the SWEETEST Fun Run in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you directly “throo” the Zoo along our popular Boo at the Zoo route.', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event is described as outdoor yoga classes at the Zoo.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "teen-friendly", "reason": "The yoga classes are designed for all fitness levels, including teens.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "Participants practice yoga near flamingos and other wildlife.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is suitable for families as it encourages participation from all ages.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "The event promotes community engagement through group fitness activities.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "sports", "reason": "Yoga is a physical activity that falls under the category of sports.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": 25, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": false, "venue_name": "Zoo"}', 'The event is an outdoor yoga class at the Zoo, suitable for families and teens, promoting fitness and community engagement.', NULL, 8039, '2026-05-10 16:00:41.992026+00'),
	('f0b10cca-bd5c-4d09-b3f8-34f7df839bb3', 'd4dfc22f-4f7f-4e8f-8895-f8f384a338c7', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Young Zoologist', 'Young Zoologist Practice your observation skills and learn what it takes to be a zoologist. Find our young zoologist stations in the Islands Zone on Thursdays between 11 a.m. and 1 p.m. to help us track the behavior of some islands mammals. We’ll work on our observation skills by marking where animals are in the exhibits and what they’re doing. Guests will also be able to test their knowledge by identifying different types of animal scat or tracks.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with Louisville Zoo membership or admission.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The program is designed for young learners.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Participants learn observation skills and about zoology.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event invites families to play, observe, and learn together.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event involves tracking animal behavior and learning about wildlife.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "storytime", "reason": "Includes story reading as part of the activities.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": 6, "age_min": 2, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is classified as free and educational for young children, focusing on zoology and nature, making it suitable for families.', NULL, 14063, '2026-05-10 16:00:57.091125+00'),
	('9925a6fe-d2dd-46bc-90bc-40faeaa9fc96', '91e23233-3c1b-421d-97a1-106bb9b32dd4', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Wildlife Photography (Spring 2026) - SOLD OUT', 'Tickets on Sale!  buy now  Saturday, May 16 from 9 – 11 a.m. $60 non-member/ $40 members  — price includes all-day admission to the Zoo!  Calling all budding photographers!    Interested in getting your start in wildlife photography? The Louisville Zoo and Murphy’s Camera are here to help!  Murphy’s Camera’s Education Coordinator Ayrica Bishop will introduce you to camera basics, the exposure triangle, composition, and how to make the most of available light. A Zoo staffer will share tips on animal behaviors to watch for and the best moments to gather dynamic action shots throughout the Zoo.  Designed for teens and adults with little to no wildlife photography experience, this hands-on session goes beyond the classroom and into the Zoo. In May, participants will begin in the MetaZoo with the smaller animals to practice techniques like photographing through glass, then head into the Africa Zone to photograph giraffes (with no visual barriers) colobus monkeys (to practice photographing through mesh) and gorillas (to practice photographing through glass). Following this itinerary, participants are free to roam the Zoo on their own to snap those special moments.  Stay tuned here for what is planned for September.  buy now   ', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "teen-friendly", "reason": "Designed for teens and adults with little to no wildlife photography experience.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Participants will learn camera basics, exposure triangle, and composition.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event takes place at the Zoo, focusing on wildlife photography.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "Participants will be photographing animals in an outdoor zoo environment.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "weekend", "reason": "Scheduled for Saturday, May 16.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "The event encourages community engagement through photography.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": 60, "age_max": null, "age_min": 13, "is_free": false, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is a wildlife photography workshop aimed at teens and adults, held at the Louisville Zoo, with a price of $60 for non-members.', NULL, 6711, '2026-05-10 16:01:04.512673+00'),
	('581e7ce8-74d3-4263-a91c-d6b5d0dcd37f', '73fd2c8a-84e9-466f-b60d-de5c5c1350a5', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Storybook Character Day (2026)', 'Saturday, May 16 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Free with Zoo admission or membership  We’re fully booked with friends like Curious George, Clifford, Pete the Cat and more! Join us as your favorite characters hop straight off the page and right to your Zoo! Character meet and greets are FREE with Zoo admission or your Louisville Zoo Membership.  Characters will rotate every 30 minutes at spots throughout the Zoo. Check signs on the day of your visit for specific character locations.  Characters appearing   Curious George Pete the Cat Clifford the Big Red Dog Paddington Bear Llama Llama Mouse (If You Give a Mouse a Cookie)    Character meet and greets are FREE with Zoo admission or your Louisville Zoo Membership.  About Meet Me at the Zoo Imagination comes to life as kids (and kids-at-heart) meet some of their favorite characters from books, movies and more throughout the Zoo during this fun event series. Character meet and greets are FREE with Zoo admission or your Louisville Zoo Membership.  You’ll have multiple opportunities throughout the year to meet some of your favorite characters.  presented by          Meet Me at the Zoo        March 28 & 29 Bunny Hop Hop over for an EGGstra fun time as you meet the Easter Bunny, hunt for eggs and more.May 16 Storybook Character Day Your favorite characters hop straight off the page and into your Zoo. Meet Curious George, Pete the Cat and more!  June 6 Super Summer Saturday Fly, jump or warp your way over to the Zoo to visit with some of your favorite superheroes, here to kick off the summer season.  July 18 Summer Santa It’s a jolly summer holiday as Santa and Mrs. Claus stop at your Zoo while on vacation  August 8 Royal Rendezvous Join some of your favorite princesses as they close out the summer season with a special soiree at the Zoo.