	('c7077d92-be35-473b-a454-316ac5b7e3ab', '84a8197f-989b-4c1e-816e-a3529e0b1adb', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Young Zoologist', 'Young Zoologist Practice your observation skills and learn what it takes to be a zoologist. Find our young zoologist stations in the Islands Zone on Thursdays between 11 a.m. and 1 p.m. to help us track the behavior of some islands mammals. We’ll work on our observation skills by marking where animals are in the exhibits and what they’re doing. Guests will also be able to test their knowledge by identifying different types of animal scat or tracks.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with Louisville Zoo membership or admission.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The program is designed for young learners.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Participants learn observation skills and about zoology.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event invites families to participate together.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event involves observing animals and their behaviors.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "playgroup", "reason": "The program includes free play and interactive activities.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": 6, "age_min": 2, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is a free educational program for young children at the Louisville Zoo, focusing on observation skills and animal behavior.', NULL, 12428, '2026-05-10 16:01:51.925739+00'),
	('6e81a8c8-a9ff-442d-842b-dcaee5dadbc4', '44f13d11-c89a-44e6-b66f-c889dbd4e6c8', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Playtime in the Cub House', 'Playtime in the Cub House Stop in and enjoy some free play time in the Cub House presented by PNC. Meet other zoo friends and play in our space, the snow leopards might even peek in to play hide and seek with you through the exhibit glass. We will open the Cub House for unstructured play time select Saturday mornings. The space will open for up to 30 people at a time to play from 10:00 a.m. to 11:30 a.m.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with Louisville Zoo membership or admission.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The event is designed for young learners and families with children.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "baby-friendly", "reason": "The activities are suitable for very young children.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "indoor", "reason": "The event takes place in the Cub House.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "weekend", "reason": "The event is held on Saturday mornings.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "The event includes learning through play and animal activity stations.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": 5, "age_min": 0, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Cub House at Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is free and designed for young children, making it suitable for toddlers and babies. It takes place indoors on weekends and includes educational activities.', NULL, 4624, '2026-05-10 16:01:56.859619+00'),
	('280b7f4c-9733-4cd1-b947-86c6bcb5730c', '6a0239c5-d7b1-47fb-afdf-1a581da3aff7', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Conservation and Conversations: Urban Wildlife', 'Guest Presenter: wildlife disease ecologist Jake Shurba, Ph.D. student with Clemson University!  Conservation AND Conversations Dates: Final Wednesday of each month Virtual sessions: Check dates for times. Sessions on Google Meet Recordings available for registered participants upon request. In-person sessions: Check dates for times and locations. Cost: FREE with admission or membership to the Louisville Zoo.   Join the conversation! Talk with Louisville Zoo staff and knowledgeable guest presenters about a variety of conservation and environmental topics. Each month will focus on a different broad topic (like healthy ecosystem function or native plant management). Discussions will be guided by an expert guest presenter or a chosen book.   Participants will receive two to four emails per month with invitations to the monthly sessions, background information on topics and speakers, links to further learning resources and media recommendations, as well as opportunities to provide program feedback. You may request to be removed from our email list at any time.    Free Online Reservation              Conservation and Conversations Schedule         Conservation and Conversations: Polar Bears International (Virtual Session) February 25, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  Excited about polar bears? Join us this month as we celebrate international polar bear day and learn from the experts at Polar Bears International about the latest research and conservation efforts for these bears and the sea ice they depend on.        Conservation and Conversations: Beaverland (Virtual) Virtual:  March 25 at 2 p.m. In-Person:  March 28 at 2 p.m.   This month we are reading Beaverland: How One Weird Rodent Made America by Leila Philip. Our discussion will center on the book and what we can learn about and from these amazing animals.       Conservation and Conversations: kNOw Waste (Virtual) April 29, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  Join us this month to learn from experts from kNOw Waste about our waste systems and the ways microplastics are spreading throughout our world.       Conservation and Conversations: Urban Wildlife May 27, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  Guest Presenter: wildlife disease ecologist Jake Shurba, Ph.D. student with Clemson University        Conservation and Conversations: Soil (Virtual) Virtual:  June 24 at 2 p.m. In-Person:  June 27 at 2 p.m.   Join us for a discussion on the book Soil: The Story of a Black Mother’s Garden by Camille T. Dungy.        Conservation and Conversations: Tigers (Virtual) July 29, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  More information coming soon! Guest Presenter to be announced.        Conservation and Conversations: Urban Green Space (Virtual) August 26, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  More information coming soon! Guest Presenter to be announced.        Conservation and Conversations: Fuzz (In Person) In-Person:  Sept. 26 at 2 p.m. Virtual:  Sept. 30 at 2 p.m.   Book Discussion on Fuzz: When Nature Breaks the Law by Mary Roach                   More Family Events       Looking for more Education Events and programs?  Learn more!', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with admission or membership to the Louisville Zoo.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "The event focuses on conservation and environmental topics with expert guest presenters.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The discussions revolve around wildlife and environmental conservation.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is designed for families to engage in discussions about wildlife and conservation.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "The event encourages community participation and conversation about conservation topics.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The event is suitable for families, including young children, to learn about wildlife.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is free with admission or membership to the Louisville Zoo and focuses on educational discussions about wildlife and conservation, making it suitable for families.', NULL, 5404, '2026-05-10 16:02:03.279658+00'),
	('02c68853-eb6c-4287-b97f-e6545249deab', '9096d803-9d32-42dc-8b0f-7d748bf7b299', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Litter Critters', 'Litter Critters Plastic is everywhere! Join us at our Litter Critter stations to learn how plastic waste effects animals and humans here in Kentucky and around the world. We’ll play games focused on recycling to earn a special sticker! These stations will be in the MetaZoo or the HerpAquarium on Wednesday afternoons in the spring.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "The event is free with Louisville Zoo membership or admission.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The program is designed for young learners.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Participants will learn about plastic waste and its effects.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event invites families to participate in activities together.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event focuses on environmental education related to animals.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "storytime", "reason": "Includes story readings as part of the activities.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": 5, "age_min": 0, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is a free educational program for young children at the Louisville Zoo, focusing on environmental awareness and family engagement.', NULL, 6926, '2026-05-10 16:02:10.839353+00'),
	('c249176f-9069-47f9-afb3-a7a54a9cd878', 'adaf1265-7556-4d77-82ae-5e614390f4c5', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Early Childhood Pop-Up:  Young Zoologist', 'Young Zoologist Practice your observation skills and learn what it takes to be a zoologist. Find our young zoologist stations in the Islands Zone on Thursdays between 11 a.m. and 1 p.m. to help us track the behavior of some islands mammals. We’ll work on our observation skills by marking where animals are in the exhibits and what they’re doing. Guests will also be able to test their knowledge by identifying different types of animal scat or tracks.  Price FREE with Louisville Zoo membership or admission  About Early Childhood Pop-ups The fun will be popping up this spring and summer at the Zoo!  Perfect for young learners, these new pop-up programs invite families and their children to play, observe and learn in new ways all while visiting the Zoo! Use your imagination during free play in the Cub House, gather around for a story reading, think like a zookeeper with animal activity stations or go on a Litter Critter quest. Pop up programs are FREE with membership or admission to the Zoo. For a full list of details and available sessions, visit our website.         EARLY CHILDHOOD POP-UPS 2026 SCHEDULE        Animal Tales Classes from 10:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.    April 19: HerpAquarium April 28: Giraffe Exhibit May 5: Islands / Little Penguin Exhibit May 12: Tiger Taiga May 19: Red Panda Exhibit  Little Critters Classes held in the MetaZoo from 3 p.m. – 5 p.m.   April 15, April 22, April 29 May 6, May 13, May 20, May 27  Playtime in the Cub House Classes held  from 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. in the Snow Leopard Cub House presented by PNC.   March 28 April 4,  April 25  (April 11 Cancelled) May 2  Young Zoologist Classes held from 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. in the Islands Zone   April 2, April 9, April 16, April 23, April 30 May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28', '["free", "outdoor