	('a43593cf-253b-4520-b87a-922c7149265d', '7bb6f6b9-683f-4998-b8ad-d042b78abfb8', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Celebrate 2026 Father’s Day at the Louisville Zoo', 'Treat dad to a day at the Zoo. In celebration of Father’s Day, all fathers receive free Zoo admission on Sunday, June 21.  Enjoy a day exploring exhibits, seeing animals up close and spending quality time together as a family. From favorite Zoo classics to seasonal animal activity, it’s an easy way to celebrate Dad.  How it works   Free admission is available to all fathers on Father’s Day Tickets are available at the Zoo only Valid for standard daytime admission Zoo hours and regular parking fees apply.', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "All fathers receive free Zoo admission on Father''s Day.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is designed for families to celebrate Father''s Day together.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "holiday", "reason": "The event is a celebration of Father''s Day, a recognized holiday.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event takes place at the Zoo, which is an outdoor venue.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "weekend", "reason": "The event occurs on a Sunday, which is a weekend.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "toddler-friendly", "reason": "The Zoo is generally suitable for families with young children.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is classified as free due to complimentary admission for fathers, and it is family-oriented, taking place outdoors at the Louisville Zoo on Father''s Day.', NULL, 6915, '2026-05-10 16:03:11.671003+00'),
	('bb01a506-285d-4224-b531-9505112dc333', 'f3fb2170-8785-438b-a7be-611113acd57e', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Wild Workout: Yoga (Glacier Run)', 'BUY NOW! Gate opens at 6 p.m. |  Class begins at 6:30 p.m.  Join us in the arctic-inspired town of Glacier Run where you may see a grizzly or polar bear wandering about. It doesn’t matter if you can BEARly touch your toes, this workout is perfect for all fitness levels.     Join us for yoga in the wild! We’re partnering with Flex Appeal to continue special Wild Workouts at your Zoo this year. We will be offering five unique outdoor yoga classes after the Zoo closes, so you can stretch in some of your favorite exhibit spaces.  For beginners and seasoned practitioners alike, these yoga classes are designed to help you increase flexibility, strengthen muscles, and improve overall health and recovery. Closed-toed shoes are strongly encouraged. Guests are also encouraged to bring a refillable water bottle that can be used at the bottle refill stations around the Zoo.  Classes are $25 each, plus a processing fee, and are available online only. All fitness levels and abilities are welcome. Tickets must be purchased online prior to the workout in order to attend.  The front gate opens at 6:00 p.m. Classes begin at 6:30 p.m.  Yoga classes on sale now! Pilates and Barre coming soon.  Prices $25 per person plus processing fee  Classes sold out in 2025 — Reserve your spot early!         FITNESS EVENTS        Throo the Zoo 5K Run/Walk 2026 May 9, 2026 @ 8:00 am  Race on over for the WILDEST 5K in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you on a safari directly “throo” the Zoo! Participants receive a t-shirt, finishers medal, post-race refreshments, PLUS a ticket to visit the Zoo at a much slower pace!       Wild Workout: Yoga (Flamingos) – SOLD OUT May 13, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Join the flamboyance during this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout. Focus on controlled movements as flamingos showcase the art of poise and balance nearby.     Wild Workout: Pilates (Red Panda) – SOLD OUT June 3, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Admire and imitate the graceful balance of our red pandas as you stretch and unwind in front of this forested exhibit space.     Wild Workout: Yoga (Glacier Run) June 22, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Join us in the arctic-inspired town of Glacier Run where you may see a grizzly or polar bear wandering about. It doesn’t matter if you can BEARly touch your toes, this workout is perfect for all fitness levels.      Wild Workout: Pilates (Giraffe) July 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on.     Wild Workout: Yoga (Butterfly) July 22, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Stretch your wings alongside our butterflies during this peaceful yoga session. Flitter inside our butterfly habitat post-workout to enjoy your animal inspiration up-close.      Wild Workout: Yoga (Colobus) August 1, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Swing by and enjoy this one-of-a-kind workout after the Zoo closes. Increase your flexibility as you enjoy the sights and sounds of our colobus monkey family peering at you from their lush habitat.      Wild Workout: Pilates (Little Penguin) August 19, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Enjoy a low-impact, muscle strengthening workout as our playful little penguins look on.      Wild Workout: Yoga (Giraffe) September 1, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on. These gentle giants will soothe your mind and help you find inner peace after a long day     Wild Workout: Pilates (Pinniped) September 9, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find your flow at this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout as you watch our playful pinnipeds (seals and sea lions).     Throo the Boo 2026 November 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Dash over and join us for the SWEETEST Fun Run in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you directly “throo” the Zoo along our popular Boo at the Zoo route.', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event is described as outdoor yoga classes in a zoo setting.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "teen-friendly", "reason": "The yoga classes are suitable for all fitness levels, including teens.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "The event takes place in a zoo, allowing participants to connect with nature.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is designed for families to participate together in a fun and healthy activity.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "The event encourages community participation in fitness and wellness.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "sports", "reason": "Yoga is a physical activity that falls under the category of sports.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": 25, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": false, "venue_name": "Glacier Run Zoo"}', 'The event is an outdoor yoga class suitable for all ages and fitness levels, held at a zoo, making it family-friendly and community-oriented. The price is set at $25 per person.', NULL, 6264, '2026-05-10 16:03:18.293154+00'),
	('79d7d8a7-6f47-45ff-959f-f0d180eafe3e', 'f7e65d1a-1c76-468e-a877-df7d74424742', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Conservation and Conversations: Soil (Virtual)', 'Join us for a discussion on the book Soil: The Story of a Black Mother’s Garden by Camille T. Dungy.  Conservation AND Conversations Dates: Final Wednesday of each month Virtual sessions: Check dates for times. Sessions on Google Meet Recordings available for registered participants upon request. In-person sessions: Check dates for times and locations. Cost: FREE with admission or membership to the Louisville Zoo.   Join the conversation! Talk with Louisville Zoo staff and knowledgeable guest presenters about a variety of conservation and environmental topics. Each month will focus on a different broad topic (like healthy ecosystem function or native plant management). Discussions will be guided by an expert guest presenter or a chosen book.   Participants will receive two to four emails per month with invitations to the monthly sessions, background information on topics and speakers, links to further learning resources and media recommendations, as well as opportunities to provide program feedback. You may request to be removed from our email list at any time.    Free Online Reservation              Conservation and Conversations Schedule         Conservation and Conversations: Polar Bears International (Virtual Session) February 25, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  Excited about polar bears? Join us this month as we celebrate international polar bear day and learn from the experts at Polar Bears International about the latest research and conservation efforts for these bears and the sea ice they depend on.        Conservation and Conversations: Beaverland (Virtual) Virtual:  March 25 at 2 p.m. In-Person:  March 28 at 2 p.m.   This month we are reading Beaverland: How One Weird Rodent Made America by Leila Philip. Our discussion will center on the book and what we can learn about and from these amazing animals.       Conservation and Conversations: kNOw Waste (Virtual) April 29, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  Join us this month to learn from experts from kNOw Waste about our waste systems and the ways microplastics are spreading throughout our world.       Conservation and Conversations: Urban Wildlife May 27, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  Guest Presenter: wildlife disease ecologist Jake Shurba, Ph.D. student with Clemson University        Conservation and Conversations: Soil (Virtual) Virtual:  June 24 at 2 p.m. In-Person:  June 27 at 2 p.m.   Join us for a discussion on the book Soil: The Story of a Black Mother’s Garden by Camille T. Dungy.        Conservation and Conversations: Tigers (Virtual) July 29, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  More information coming soon! Guest Presenter to be announced.        Conservation and Conversations: Urban Green Space (Virtual) August 26, 2026 @ 2:00 pm  More information coming soon! Guest Presenter to be announced.        Conservation and Conversations: Fuzz (In Person) In-Person:  Sept. 26 at 2 p.m. Virtual:  Sept. 30 at 2 p.m.   Book Discussion on Fuzz: When Nature Breaks the Law by Mary Roach                   More Family Events       Looking for more Education Events and programs?  Learn more!', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "free", "reason": "Cost: FREE with admission or membership to the Louisville Zoo.", "confidence": 1, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Discussions will focus on conservation and environmental topics.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "Participants will engage with Louisville Zoo staff and guest presenters.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "Topics include co