ipants will engage with Louisville Zoo staff and guest presenters.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "Topics include healthy ecosystem function and native plant management.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "indoor", "reason": "In-person sessions will take place indoors at the Louisville Zoo.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is free with admission to the Louisville Zoo and focuses on educational discussions about conservation, making it suitable for families and community engagement.', NULL, 5382, '2026-05-10 16:03:29.44231+00'),
	('30b6b73e-8089-43d8-999f-8750651b15e8', 'de0cc88c-35f2-4b97-aba7-159c8722cd76', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'Wild Workout: Pilates (Giraffe)', 'BUY NOW! Gate opens at 6 p.m. |  Class begins at 6:30 p.m.  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on. These gentle giants will soothe your mind and help you find inner peace after a long day.    Join us for phyiscal fun in the wild! We’re partnering with Flex Appeal to continue special Wild Workouts at your Zoo this year. We will be offering five unique outdoor classes after the Zoo closes, so you can stretch in some of your favorite exhibit spaces.  For beginners and seasoned practitioners alike, these classes are designed to help you increase flexibility, strengthen muscles, and improve overall health and recovery. Closed-toed shoes are strongly encouraged. Guests are also encouraged to bring a refillable water bottle that can be used at the bottle refill stations around the Zoo.  Classes are $25 each, plus a processing fee, and are available online only. All fitness levels and abilities are welcome. Tickets must be purchased online prior to the workout in order to attend.  The front gate opens at 6:00 p.m. Classes begin at 6:30 p.m.  Prices $25 per person plus processing fee  Classes sold out in 2025 — Reserve your spot early!         FITNESS EVENTS        Throo the Zoo 5K Run/Walk 2026 May 9, 2026 @ 8:00 am  Race on over for the WILDEST 5K in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you on a safari directly “throo” the Zoo! Participants receive a t-shirt, finishers medal, post-race refreshments, PLUS a ticket to visit the Zoo at a much slower pace!       Wild Workout: Yoga (Flamingos) – SOLD OUT May 13, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Join the flamboyance during this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout. Focus on controlled movements as flamingos showcase the art of poise and balance nearby.     Wild Workout: Pilates (Red Panda) – SOLD OUT June 3, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Admire and imitate the graceful balance of our red pandas as you stretch and unwind in front of this forested exhibit space.     Wild Workout: Yoga (Glacier Run) June 22, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Join us in the arctic-inspired town of Glacier Run where you may see a grizzly or polar bear wandering about. It doesn’t matter if you can BEARly touch your toes, this workout is perfect for all fitness levels.      Wild Workout: Pilates (Giraffe) July 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on.     Wild Workout: Yoga (Butterfly) July 22, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Stretch your wings alongside our butterflies during this peaceful yoga session. Flitter inside our butterfly habitat post-workout to enjoy your animal inspiration up-close.      Wild Workout: Yoga (Colobus) August 1, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Swing by and enjoy this one-of-a-kind workout after the Zoo closes. Increase your flexibility as you enjoy the sights and sounds of our colobus monkey family peering at you from their lush habitat.      Wild Workout: Pilates (Little Penguin) August 19, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Enjoy a low-impact, muscle strengthening workout as our playful little penguins look on.      Wild Workout: Yoga (Giraffe) September 1, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find inspiration in nature as you stretch and strike a pose with our giraffe herd looking on. These gentle giants will soothe your mind and help you find inner peace after a long day     Wild Workout: Pilates (Pinniped) September 9, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Find your flow at this low-impact, muscle strengthening workout as you watch our playful pinnipeds (seals and sea lions).     Throo the Boo 2026 November 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Dash over and join us for the SWEETEST Fun Run in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you directly “throo” the Zoo along our popular Boo at the Zoo route.', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event is described as an outdoor class at the Zoo.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "nature", "reason": "Participants will be inspired by nature and the giraffe herd during the workout.", "confidence": 0.85, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "The event promotes community engagement through fitness in a natural setting.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "teen-friendly", "reason": "The class is designed for all fitness levels, including teens.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "educational", "reason": "Participants may learn about fitness and animal behavior during the class.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": 25, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": false, "venue_name": "Zoo"}', 'The event is an outdoor Pilates class at the Zoo, promoting fitness and community engagement, with a price of $25.', NULL, 4407, '2026-05-10 16:03:34.162307+00'),
	('b74fb9a4-4d4e-4ece-a13d-acd77003f7da', '5666434c-5922-4a9b-a9a2-5952db2ed502', '78b8cbbd-eaf6-4df7-be6d-17777e56684b', 'import', 'openai', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'success', 'ROARchestra 2026', 'SAVE THE DATE! ROARchestra is back! The Louisville Orchestra and your Louisville Zoo have partnered together again to present a wildly entertaining musical evening. Bring your blanket or lawn chairs and enjoy live music under the stars at the Zoo’s Oasis stage.  More information coming soon!           FAMILY FRIENDLY EVENTS        Bunny Hop March 28 & 29, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Hop over for an EGGstra fun time as you meet the Easter Bunny, hunt for eggs and more.      Kentucky Shakespeare – The Tempest April 4, 2026 @ 11:00 am  Kentucky Shakespeare, the Official Shakespeare Festival of Kentucky, presents THE TEMPEST at the Louisville Zoo.     VIP (Very Important Princesses) Party 2026 April 11 & 12, 2026 Sessions at 9 a.m. and 12 p.m.   The Louisville Zoo invites all our VIPs (Very Important Princesses and Princes) to a royal banquet straight out of a fairytale. Join princesses from every kingdom for an enchanting storybook celebration.      Native Plant Sale (April 2026) April 19, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Browse a selection of native plants available for purchase at the Zoo.     Throo the Zoo 5K Run/Walk 2026 May 9, 2026 @ 8:00 am  Race on over for the WILDEST 5K in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you on a safari directly “throo” the Zoo! Participants receive a t-shirt, finishers medal, post-race refreshments, PLUS a ticket to visit the Zoo at a much slower pace!      Storybook Character Day (2026) May 16, 2026 @ 10:00 am  We’re fully booked with friends like Curious George, Clifford, Pete the Cat and more! Join us as your favorite characters hop straight off the page and right to your Zoo!     Super Summer Saturday (2026) June 6, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Fly, jump or warp your way over to the Zoo to visit with some of your favorite superheroes, here to kick off the summer season. While at the Zoo, learn about some of the amazing adaptations your favorite animals harness as their own wild “superpowers”.     ROARchestra 2026 July 11, 2026 @ 8:30 pm  ROARchestra is back! The Louisville Orchestra and your Louisville Zoo have partnered together again to present a wildly entertaining musical evening. Bring your blanket or lawn chairs and enjoy live music under the stars at the Zoo’s renovated Oasis stage.     Summer Santa (2026) July 18, 2026 @ 10:00 am  It’s a jolly summer holiday as Santa and Mrs. Claus stop at your Zoo while on vacation. Join them to get your holiday list in early.     Royal Rendezvous (2026) August 8, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Princesses have arrived from faraway lands to close out the summer season with all of their adoring (and adorable) subjects. Ball gowns are not required, but guests are welcome to dress their best for this Royal Rendezvous.     Cinema Safari 2026 – Zootopia 2 August 14, 2026 @ 8:00 pm  Hey bub, grab your partners-in-crime (or crime-fighting) and join Judy and Nick as they try to make the world a better place.     Cinema Safari 2026 – Wicked For Good September 4, 2026 @ 8:00 pm  We’re bubbling with excitement for the finale to the hit musical starring Cynthia Erivo and Ariana Grande.     Native Plant Sale (September 2026) September 13, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Browse a selection of native plants available for purchase at the Zoo. Whether you’re just starting out or have been gardening for years, you are sure to find the perfect plants to benefit the pollinators that visit your at-home habitat.      La Fiesta at the Zoo: A Latin American Heritage Celebration (2026) September 19, 2026 @ 10:00 am  Join the Louisville Zoo for a fun celebración! Partners from throughout our community will be here to share information and resources, festive music, vibrant art and more.     Boo at the Zoo (2026) October 1 – 29 (Select nights)  Join us for the sweetest party in town! Boo at the Zoo features trick-or-treating for kids 11-and-under, rides, and special attractions all for one great price.     Boo at the Zoo 2026 – Sensory Friendly Night October 7, 2026 @ 5:00 pm  This special night features peanut-free treat booths and added non-food treats like stickers, tattoos, pencils and more.     Boo at the Zoo 2026 – Allergy Friendly Night October 28, 2026 @ 5:00 pm  This special night features peanut-free treat booths and added non-food treats like stickers, tattoos, pencils and more.     Día de los Muertos (2026) November 1 & 2, 2026  The Louisville Zoo is creating a special ofrenda for Día de los Muertos (the Day of the Dead) to honor beloved pets and Zoo animals that have passed away–animals who brought joy to our guests, inspired our mission, and touched the hearts of staff.     Throo the Boo 2026 November 7, 2026 @ 6:00 pm  Dash over and join us for the SWEETEST Fun Run in Louisville! This unique course doesn’t just go around the Zoo but takes you directly “throo” the Zoo along our popular Boo at the Zoo route.     Beary Happy Holidays (2026) December 5-6 December 12 – 13 December 19-20 (Santa & Mrs. Claus)   Throughout December, we’re transforming areas of your Zoo into a winter wonderland, complete with holiday-themed decorations and animal enrichment.             ', '["free", "outdoor", "indoor", "toddler-friendly", "baby-friendly", "teen-friendly", "weekend", "educational", "arts-crafts", "music", "sensory-friendly", "family-festival", "storytime", "stem", "sports", "cooking", "nature", "community", "holiday", "playgroup"]', '[{"slug": "music", "reason": "The event features live music performed by the Louisville Orchestra.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "family-festival", "reason": "The event is described as family-friendly and encourages families to attend.", "confidence": 0.9, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "outdoor", "reason": "The event takes place under the stars at the Zoo’s Oasis stage.", "confidence": 0.8, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "holiday", "reason": "The event is part of a series of family-friendly events at the Zoo, including holiday-themed activities.", "confidence": 0.7, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "community", "reason": "The event promotes community engagement through music and family activities.", "confidence": 0.6, "matched_keywords": []}, {"slug": "weekend", "reason": "The event is scheduled for a weekend evening.", "confidence": 0.5, "matched_keywords": []}]', '{"price": null, "age_max": null, "age_min": null, "is_free": true, "venue_name": "Louisville Zoo"}', 'The event is classified based on its musical nature, outdoor setting, family-friendly focus, and community engagement. It is free to attend, making it accessible for families.', NULL, 5892, '2026-05-10 16:03:40.34056+00');
